  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6560.94 sitting below the 6581 flip line in a PIN regime, dealers are positioned as stabilizers and will likely buy any dip toward the 6550 negative gamma wall while selling strength into the massive 34B positive gamma at 6580. The recent GEX surge (23.5% 1-min, 71.8% 5-min) suggests heavy options flow that's reinforcing the current range-bound setup between 6550-6580, with dealers expected to provide liquidity against directional moves. Watch for mean reversion behavior as dealers defend the 6550 support aggressively while capping upside momentum at the 6580 level where they'll increase selling pressure.",
